          <p>Louisiana's summer heat is no joke—temperatures regularly exceed 95°F with humidity that makes it feel even hotter. A broken air conditioner isn't just uncomfortable; it can be dangerous for children, elderly family members, and pets. That's why we offer 24/7 emergency AC repair and typically arrive within 1-2 hours in Lake Charles.</p>

          <h2>Common AC Problems We Repair</h2>
          <p>Our NATE-certified technicians diagnose and repair all types of air conditioning problems:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>AC Not Cooling:</strong> The most common complaint. Could be low refrigerant, dirty coils, compressor issues, or thermostat problems.</li>
            <li><strong>AC Not Turning On:</strong> Often caused by electrical issues, capacitor failure, or thermostat malfunctions.</li>
            <li><strong>AC Blowing Warm Air:</strong> Usually indicates refrigerant leaks, compressor problems, or airflow restrictions.</li>
            <li><strong>Strange Noises:</strong> Grinding, squealing, or banging sounds indicate mechanical problems that need immediate attention.</li>
            <li><strong>AC Short Cycling:</strong> Frequent on/off cycling often means an oversized unit, refrigerant issues, or electrical problems.</li>
            <li><strong>High Humidity:</strong> AC running but not removing humidity properly may need coil cleaning or refrigerant charge.</li>
            <li><strong>Water Leaks:</strong> Clogged drain lines, frozen coils, or condensate pump failures.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice on AC Unit:</strong> Low refrigerant, poor airflow, or dirty coils can cause ice buildup.</li>
          </ul>

